{"TopicId":5741,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"BTV Inc. Presents: The happypod V1.1","CreatedByName":"xzbobzx","CreatedById":10586,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-01-18T19:31:15Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"xzbobzx","CreatedById":10586,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-01-18T19:31:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBob Television Incorporated is proud to present to you;\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe first ever mod by Bob \\\u0027xzbobzx\\\u0027 Kowalski;\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWith jeb\\\u0027s approval;\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETHE HAPPYPOD\u003Csub\u003Ev1.0\u003C/sub\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EClick spoiler for images:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img35.imageshack.us/img35/6839/happy3.png\u0022 alt=\u0022happy3.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img19.imageshack.us/img19/2240/happy1q.png\u0022 alt=\u0022happy1q.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img42.imageshack.us/img42/9792/happy4u.png\u0022 alt=\u0022happy4u.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYea, that\\\u0027s right, it\\\u0027s a giant head thing, and it\\\u0027s name is John.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt\\\u0027s my first working mod and I\\\u0027m pretty pleased with the result myself.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAnyway, enjoy John!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-decoration:line-through;\u0022\u003EEdit: yes, I am mighty well aware that the happypod has no room for parachutes, but then again who would enjoy a parachute stuck to the top of their head?\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEdit\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E: Version 1.1 features a node on top of John\\\u0027s head for parachute placement.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003EYou have the right to retexture, modify, or otherwise use it in works of your own, if you are willing to give credit.\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bandit4910","CreatedById":14446,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-01-18T19:42:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022xzbobzx\u0022 data-cite=\u0022xzbobzx\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBob Television Incorporated is proud to present to you;\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe first ever mod by Bob \\\u0027xzbobzx\\\u0027 Kowalski;\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWith jeb\\\u0027s approval;\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETHE HAPPYPOD\u003Csub\u003Ev1.0\u003C/sub\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EClick spoiler for images:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img35.imageshack.us/img35/6839/happy3.png\u0022 alt=\u0022happy3.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img19.imageshack.us/img19/2240/happy1q.png\u0022 alt=\u0022happy1q.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img692.imageshack.us/img692/151/happy2a.png\u0022 alt=\u0022happy2a.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYea, that\\\u0027s right, it\\\u0027s a giant head thing.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt\\\u0027s my first working mod and I\\\u0027m pretty pleased with the result myself.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAnyway, enjoy this.. thing.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEdit: yes, I am mighty well aware that the happypod has no room for parachutes, but then again who would enjoy a parachute stuck to the top of their head?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhy not make the head thingy a parachute?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOr, if possible make the head have the rocket float in the water...\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"xzbobzx","CreatedById":10586,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-01-18T19:47:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022joey73101\u0022 data-cite=\u0022joey73101\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhy not make the head thingy a parachute?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOr, if possible make the head have the rocket float in the water...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBecause I have \u003Cem\u003Eno idea\u003C/em\u003E how to make parachutes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlso I could make an aquatic, and nearly indestructible version of the happypod.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYou could also use radial chutes and a sas module below it or something, or do a powerlanding.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"iamwearingpants","CreatedById":27,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-01-18T19:49:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ESomeone needs to re-texture this like Jeb\\\u0027s head. \u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tosh","CreatedById":11055,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-01-18T19:54:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ECongratulations on first release))\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022xzbobzx\u0022 data-cite=\u0022xzbobzx\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEdit: yes, I am mighty well aware that the happypod has no room for parachutes, but then again who would enjoy a parachute stuck to the top of their head?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWell, a fancy hat would be just fine \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022xzbobzx\u0022 data-cite=\u0022xzbobzx\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBecause I have \u003Cem\u003Eno idea\u003C/em\u003E how to make parachutes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETo get that idea you may import a standard one (you\\\u0027ll need to \\\u0027fix\\\u0027 it afterwards as described in \u003Ca href=\u0022http://kerbalspaceprogram.com/forum/index.php?topic=6109.0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ethis topic\u003C/a\u003E). Or use a canopy of Gemini chute, it\\\u0027s created with Blender and will need no fixing. Yes, you have an author\\\u0027s permission.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"xzbobzx","CreatedById":10586,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-01-18T19:55:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022iamwearingpants\u0022 data-cite=\u0022iamwearingpants\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESomeone needs to re-texture this like Jeb\\\u0027s head.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI think I can supply you with the empty UV Projection, lemme look around.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEdit: There we go:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://img848.imageshack.us/img848/8735/cmdpod1.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://img848.imageshack.us/img848/8735/cmdpod1.png\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWarning, it\\\u0027s huge.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"semininja","CreatedById":3837,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-01-18T20:24:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYou could put a chute stack node far enough inside that the chute doesn\\\u0027t show until deployed...\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Heyheyzx","CreatedById":10770,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-01-18T20:27:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI have an idea, why don\\\u0027t you make parachutes that looks like hats!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Luigibro606","CreatedById":8700,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-01-18T21:24:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Heyheyzx\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Heyheyzx\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI have an idea, why don\\\u0027t you make parachutes that looks like hats!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis guy... he\\\u0027s on to something! Make hat \\\u0027chutes please.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Technical Ben","CreatedById":10512,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-01-18T22:05:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022xzbobzx\u0022 data-cite=\u0022xzbobzx\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBecause I have \u003Cem\u003Eno idea\u003C/em\u003E how to make parachutes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlso I could make an aquatic, and nearly indestructible version of the happypod.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYou could also use radial chutes and a sas module below it or something, or do a powerlanding.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAnd.... I\\\u0027ll not get the time to make a video on how to make parachutes for a while. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBut, on the bright side, funny mod there! Quite good for a first attempt. I mean, it worked right!? That\\\u0027s success! First step on the long ladder to \u003Cspan style=\u0022text-decoration:line-through;\u0022\u003Efailure\u003C/span\u003E \u003Cspan style=\u0022text-decoration:line-through;\u0022\u003E boredom \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E success!!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHats are good too!!!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"semininja","CreatedById":3837,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-01-19T01:41:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ESuggestion 2: different flavors!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"White Owl","CreatedById":10849,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-01-19T03:20:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI like it.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Goddess Bhavani","CreatedById":14001,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-01-19T03:36:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://www.cmdshiftdesign.com/blog_images/061208/legoman.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022legoman.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENow, we can make flying Lego Gundams, Kerbal style!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"xzbobzx","CreatedById":10586,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-01-19T14:43:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EHats.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe thought of having to make a hat scares me.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI barely managed to create this thing, but alright, I\\\u0027ll give it a go.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Luigibro606","CreatedById":8700,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-01-19T16:32:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIt needs a top hat!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"xzbobzx","CreatedById":10586,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-01-19T18:31:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EAlright alright, you guys will get your top hat.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAdded a parachute node for now, I\\\u0027ll get to work on the hat.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEdit: yeah somebody supply me with a blender parachute tutorial, plz?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Heyheyzx","CreatedById":10770,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-01-19T19:26:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWe also need a propeller beanie!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"xzbobzx","CreatedById":10586,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-01-19T19:34:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Heyheyzx\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Heyheyzx\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWe also need a propeller beanie!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELOL \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E